57. (1) The Bank may specify standards on prudential matters
to promote—
(a) the sound financial position of an institution; or
(b) integrity, professionalism and expertise in the conduct of
the business, affairs and activities of an institution.
(2) Without limiting the generality of subsection (1), standards
specified under that subsection may include standards relating to—
(a) capital adequacy;
(b) liquidity;
(c) corporate governance;
(d) risk management;
(e) related party transactions;
(f) maintenance of reserve funds;
(g) takaful funds; and
(h) prevention of an institution from being used, intentionally
or unintentionally, for criminal activities.
(3) For purposes of paragraph (2)(e), “related party transactions”
means transactions with an institution involving—
(a) a director, officer or shareholder of the institution;
(b) a member of the Shariah committee of the institution;
Islamic Financial Services                              87
(c) any person in a position to influence or control the
institution or affect the decisions of the institution;
(d) a relative or dependent of any person referred to in
paragraph (a), (b) or (c); or
(e) any other person as may be specified by the Bank, which
in the opinion of the Bank may cause the institution to
be in a conflict of interest situation.
